main event: Ground radar detected an unidentified object at Nellis AFB, Nevada on 18 April 1962, but there were no visual observations.
interesting points: The object was detected by ground radar but not visually observed.,The report stated the object was tracked for 55 minutes.,Insufficient data in the report makes it challenging to form a valid conclusion.,The characteristics suggested the object may have been a balloon.,There were multiple attempts to gather information from various Air Force departments regarding the sighting.
witness description: No visual witnesses reported in conjunction with radar detection.
